Looks to be at 96+ - 98+%, only two faint and difficult to see tiny wear marks at front edge of slide. Comes with its original German/English handbook. No box or papers, etc.  See Picture. 

This Walther TPH serial # is 2890XX. Please don't mistake this gem specimen TPH for the US stainless steel clones. This TPH is from my personal collection and is the exceedingly scarce and collectible high quality 100% German made version in mint/gem condition. If your safety requires the finest small back-up pistol in existence or if you simply desire a tangible investment that is guaranteed to grow in value -- the German made TPH is for you. 

The German made version of the TPH is very rare and expensive because of the 1968 Gun Control Act ( GCA ) One provision of the GCA stipulated that all firearms imported into the US must "be generally recognized as particularly suitable for or readily adaptable to sporting purposes." As interpreted by BATF, the Walther TPH pistol did not meet the "sporting purposes" criteria provision and was thus permanently banned from US importation ( except under rare circumstances as outlined below ). 

Since Walther did not start manufacturing the TPH until early 1968, Interarms was only able to legally import a minimal number of German made TPHs prior to the GCA effective date of 10/22/68. Since then, only a few TPHs have been legally imported into the US ( on an ATF Form 6 ) by either returning US servicemen or German immigrants. 

Because of their scarcity, the current value of authentic German manufactured TPH pistols is many times the original MSRP and continues to appreciate. Walther designed the TPH to serve as a "back-up" weapon for law enforcement officers. However, due to their value, these days few TPHs are actually carried. The vast majority of German made TPHs reside safely in the vaults of knowledgeable investors. 

This TPH exhibits German craftsmanship through out. It has a highly polished deep blue finish, fixed contrast sights, checkered black synthetic grips and the original TPH owners manual.

Stock has a professionally repaired 3 1/4' hairline crack. Work done by our Master Gunsmith/Engraver, Larry Cole. His work had been featured in many magazine covers , articles and NRA Presentation Firearms. 

The Savage 99 was preceded by the Savage 1895, which was the first hammerless lever-action rifle produced. The hammerless design is a substantial improvement because the time from trigger pull to firing is less. This makes the rifle more accurate, because the rifleman's muscular tremors have less time to move the rifle off-aim. A hammerless design is also less likely to jam in brush or clothing. 

The magazine design allowed the rifle to be one of the first lever-action rifles to use spitzer bullets. Previous lever-action rifles used tubular magazines, which placed cartridges of ammunition end to end. With spitzer bullets, the pointed tips of the ammunition would contact the primer of the cartridge in front of it, possibly causing an accidental discharge. Another novel safety feature- upon cocking the rifle, a small pin would protrude above the top receiver to indicate the rifle was cocked and ready to fire.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger Security Six 2 3/4" 357 Magnum SS
postcontent:
$600 OBO, OBO!!!! This is a highly collectable Ruger Security Six 2 3/4" barrel 357 Magnum in Stainless Steel. This gun is in 99% condition, I say 99% as it is used but not much!!! No rust, scratches, or any other issues. It is flawless.

When I say highly collectable, first off it was made in 1975, this was the first year Ruger made this gun in Stainless Steel, also this is a PRE-WARNING revolver. In 1977 Ruger started put warning stamps on the barrel stating to read owners manuel etc... before using the gun. My gun has no warning, lastly it is the snub nose version made with a 2 3/4" barrel, these are alot harder to come by as the production numbers on these length barrels were very limited. It has adjustable sights as well. Try and find a 2 3/4" Pre warning in this condition, you wont, I searched two years before I found this one and it was a fluke, they are just not out there for sale very often???

I have a nice pair of Hogue Grips on the gun and I also have the original wooden grips, the original grips are mint condition. This gun has been fired very little and lockup is super tight and the trigger in single action is crisp, so crisp and light it is amazing. One of the best pistols I have ever owned and fired. Selling it to fund another project!

Lastly this gun comes with a handmade leather holster, this holster was special made for this gun and the two combine for a excellent carry piece.
This gun also comes with two Dade speed loaders and some ammo.

I will accept reasonable offers on this gun package. Additional pictures available upon request. Wichita area only FTF

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger SS 357 Mag
postcontent:
$600 OBO: This is a highly collectable Ruger Security Six 2 3/4" barrel 357 Magnum in Stainless Steel. This gun is in 99% condition, I say 99% as it is used but not much!!! No rust, scratches, or any other issues. It is flawless.

When I say highly collectable, first off it was made in 1975, this was the first year Ruger made this gun in Stainless Steel, also this is a PRE-WARNING revolver. In 1977 Ruger started put warning stamps on the barrel stating to read owners manuel etc... before using the gun. My gun has no warning, lastly it is the snub nose version made with a 2 3/4" barrel, these are alot harder to come by as the production numbers on these length barrels were very limited. It has adjustable sights as well. Try and find a 2 3/4" Pre warning in this condition, you wont, I searched two years before I found this one and it was a fluke, they are just not out there for sale very often???

I have a nice pair of Hogue Grips on the gun and I also have the original wooden grips, the original grips are mint condition. This gun has been fired very little and lockup is super tight and the trigger in single action is crisp, so crisp and light it is amazing. One of the best pistols I have ever owned and fired. Selling it to fund another project!

Lastly this gun comes with a handmade leather holster, this holster was special made for this gun and the two combine for a excellent carry piece.
This gun also comes with two Dade speed loaders and some ammo.

I will accept reasonable offers on this gun package. Additional pictures available upon request. Wichita area only FTF
